1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:10,000
[Skip to 2:48. Opening Theme Music - Full translation available in Ep. 1]

2
00:00:10,000 --> 00:00:22,000
Mojo Mojo Mojo Spy

3
00:00:22,000 --> 00:00:23,000
Let's go.

4
00:00:23,000 --> 00:00:26,000
This world is flooded with colors.

5
00:00:26,000 --> 00:00:29,000
Twisting and shaking, confusing our eyes.

6
00:00:29,000 --> 00:00:32,219
Look with your heart, and see clearly.

7
00:00:32,219 --> 00:00:35,200
The truth is right in the courtyard.

8
00:00:35,200 --> 00:00:38,219
Hey you, good or bad, truth or lies

9
00:00:38,219 --> 00:00:41,200
Can't escape this gray smoke of the soul.

10
00:00:41,200 --> 00:00:44,219
Pack up all your courage.

11
00:00:44,219 --> 00:00:47,219
Maybe we can save this world.

12
00:00:47,219 --> 00:00:49,539
Mojo Mojo Mojo Spy

13
00:00:49,539 --> 00:00:52,960
Mojo Mojo Mojo Spy

14
00:00:52,960 --> 00:00:55,900
Mojo Mojo Mojo Spy

15
00:00:55,900 --> 00:00:57,159
I'm ready to translate. Please provide the Chinese subtitles you'd like me to work on.

16
00:01:08,000 --> 00:01:09,659
Late at night.

17
00:01:09,659 --> 00:01:11,159
A black-clad robber

18
00:01:11,159 --> 00:01:12,859
Robbed Ms. Taylor's house.

19
00:01:12,859 --> 00:01:14,159
But only kidnapped

20
00:01:14,159 --> 00:01:15,039
Her little dog.

21
00:01:15,039 --> 00:01:16,219
And Taylor...

22
00:01:16,219 --> 00:01:17,480
Due to extreme fright

23
00:01:17,480 --> 00:01:18,640
Was taken to the hospital.

24
00:01:18,640 --> 00:01:19,879
The next day

25
00:01:19,879 --> 00:01:21,079
Locky Qi and the others

26
00:01:21,079 --> 00:01:22,120
Heading to Tyler's place

27
00:01:22,120 --> 00:01:23,079
to investigate.

28
00:01:23,079 --> 00:01:26,700
The beauty pageant mystery.

29
00:01:29,659 --> 00:01:32,060
A special dog... a little too special.

30
00:01:32,060 --> 00:01:33,920
Where did you go?

31
00:01:33,060 --> 00:01:34,920
To pee.

32
00:01:33,920 --> 00:01:38,180
Drink that much juice again, and I'm not taking you on cases anymore.

33
00:01:38,180 --> 00:01:40,319
What's that in your hand?

34
00:01:40,319 --> 00:01:42,900
This? Jingjing just found it.

35
00:01:42,900 --> 00:01:45,000
Looks like it's related to that cute dog.

36
00:01:45,519 --> 00:01:51,920
Drink that much juice again, and I won't get to come on cases?

37
00:01:59,000 --> 00:02:01,560
Ms. Tyler, hello.

38
00:02:01,560 --> 00:02:03,659
The First National Beautiful Dog Contest

39
00:02:03,659 --> 00:02:05,459
cordially invites you and your dog

40
00:02:05,459 --> 00:02:06,739
to participate.

41
00:02:06,739 --> 00:02:10,659
This might be a clue.

42
00:02:10,659 --> 00:02:13,939
I'm really worried about my mom.

43
00:02:13,939 --> 00:02:16,560
I need to go see her in the hospital.

44
00:02:16,560 --> 00:02:19,580
Yeah, I think we should hit the hospital too

45
00:02:19,580 --> 00:02:21,900
to check on Ms. Tyler's condition.

46
00:02:21,900 --> 00:02:23,020
And once she wakes up,

47
00:02:23,020 --> 00:02:24,300
we might be able to get

48
00:02:24,300 --> 00:02:25,259
more clues.

49
00:02:25,259 --> 00:02:27,159
How about we split into three teams?

50
00:02:27,159 --> 00:02:28,159
Officer Sima, you take one.

51
00:02:28,159 --> 00:02:30,159
Accompany Mr. Niake to the hospital.

52
00:02:30,159 --> 00:02:32,379
Me, Locky, and Jingjing

53
00:02:32,379 --> 00:02:35,000
will head to the competition registration to check things out.

54
00:02:35,000 --> 00:02:38,639
Hawxing will stay at Shuiyunli

55
00:02:38,639 --> 00:02:40,719
in case the criminal calls.

56
00:02:40,719 --> 00:02:41,479
Sorry,

57
00:02:41,479 --> 00:02:44,319
I need to investigate other leads my own way.

58
00:02:44,319 --> 00:02:47,479
Hmph, so proper.

59
00:02:47,479 --> 00:02:56,240
Main computer, activate geographic navigation.

60
00:02:56,240 --> 00:02:56,960
Yes.

61
00:02:56,960 --> 00:03:01,300
Lock onto Tuna Hospital Emergency Data Center.

62
00:03:01,300 --> 00:03:02,700
Locking in.

63
00:03:14,700 --> 00:03:16,280
Mr. Niake,

64
00:03:16,280 --> 00:03:17,680
don't worry too much.

65
00:03:17,680 --> 00:03:21,200
The doctor said the old lady just got a scare.

66
00:03:21,200 --> 00:03:23,120
She'll wake up soon.

67
00:03:26,960 --> 00:03:34,960
L-L-L-Little Kitten, Little Kitten.

68
00:03:34,960 --> 00:03:38,960
Doctor, doctor, hurry, the patient's awake!

69
00:04:04,960 --> 00:04:05,840
Password cracked successfully.

70
00:04:05,840 --> 00:04:07,200
Copying data.

71
00:04:48,959 --> 00:04:50,659
Preparing data input.

72
00:04:50,659 --> 00:04:52,759
Cross-referencing emergency center communication logs.

73
00:04:52,759 --> 00:04:53,599
Yes.

74
00:04:53,600 --> 00:04:59,780
You emotionless monster.

75
00:04:59,780 --> 00:05:09,080
Start cracking the police database.

76
00:05:09,080 --> 00:05:11,260
Trace the address source of the suspicious number.

77
00:05:11,260 --> 00:05:12,020
Yes

78
00:05:23,600 --> 00:05:28,240
Oh, hello there!

79
00:05:28,240 --> 00:05:31,120
Just got your call.

80
00:05:31,120 --> 00:05:32,900
Didn't expect you to show up so soon.

81
00:05:32,900 --> 00:05:35,800
Please follow me to my data room first.

82
00:05:35,800 --> 00:05:36,580
Go ahead.

83
00:05:36,580 --> 00:05:44,260
Mr. Hao, I'm really sorry to trouble you.

84
00:05:44,260 --> 00:05:45,939
We need info on a contest dog.

85
00:05:45,939 --> 00:05:47,060
It's name is Little Kitten.

86
00:05:47,060 --> 00:05:49,060
Master is Ms. Taylor.

87
00:05:49,060 --> 00:05:51,379
Ah, I remember. Just a moment.

88
00:05:51,379 --> 00:05:58,459
Check this out.

89
00:05:59,379 --> 00:06:00,459
Hey, this—

90
00:06:02,459 --> 00:06:03,620
All letters and numbers.

91
00:06:03,620 --> 00:06:05,079
Top secret files?

92
00:06:05,079 --> 00:06:07,579
Too many people signed up.

93
00:06:07,579 --> 00:06:09,600
This is totally beyond our expectations.

94
00:06:09,600 --> 00:06:13,159
So in the end, we all went with numbers.

95
00:06:13,159 --> 00:06:15,860
Now it's so complicated that even I can't keep track anymore.

96
00:06:17,779 --> 00:06:20,019
Anyone else can see this data?

97
00:06:20,019 --> 00:06:23,359
Just me and three staff members.

98
00:06:23,359 --> 00:06:24,319
Those staff members

99
00:06:24,319 --> 00:06:26,319
Has there been anything unusual lately?

100
00:06:26,319 --> 00:06:27,379
Oh, hehe, they...

101
00:06:27,379 --> 00:06:29,199
They've been way too busy lately.

102
00:06:29,199 --> 00:06:30,120
When it was time to clock out,

103
00:06:30,120 --> 00:06:31,240
I told them to go home.

104
00:06:31,240 --> 00:06:32,979
They actually insisted on working overtime,

105
00:06:32,979 --> 00:06:35,259
and even slept in the office.

106
00:06:35,259 --> 00:06:36,740
Looks like nothing unusual.

107
00:06:36,740 --> 00:06:37,659
I'll take my leave now.

108
00:06:37,659 --> 00:06:39,199
Thanks for your help.

109
00:06:39,199 --> 00:06:39,699
Alright.

110
00:06:39,699 --> 00:06:41,699
Feel free to contact me if anything comes up.

111
00:06:45,639 --> 00:06:46,039
Hello? (answering phone)

112
00:06:46,039 --> 00:06:47,159
She's left the hospital.

113
00:06:47,159 --> 00:06:47,519
Okay.

114
00:06:47,519 --> 00:06:48,539
We'll be right there.

115
00:06:48,539 --> 00:06:49,659
Yeah, got it.

116
00:06:49,660 --> 00:06:50,460
Understood.

117
00:06:50,460 --> 00:06:54,380
Let's go—we're heading back to Niake's place.

118
00:06:54,380 --> 00:06:56,320
The old lady's been discharged and is home now.

119
00:07:04,760 --> 00:07:06,260
Has Ms. Taylor returned?

120
00:07:06,260 --> 00:07:09,180
Ms. Taylor went to her room to rest.

121
00:07:09,180 --> 00:07:11,080
How is she?

122
00:07:11,080 --> 00:07:13,220
Niake's mother's health—

123
00:07:13,220 --> 00:07:14,180
nothing serious.

124
00:07:14,180 --> 00:07:16,040
She's just really worried about her little dog,

125
00:07:16,040 --> 00:07:17,460
insisted on coming home to wait.

126
00:07:17,460 --> 00:07:19,500
She didn't get a clear look at the suspect's face.

127
00:07:19,500 --> 00:07:21,660
The criminal hasn't called either.

128
00:07:21,660 --> 00:07:23,160
Any leads on your end?

129
00:07:23,160 --> 00:07:25,220
Locky Qi,

130
00:07:25,220 --> 00:07:26,879
got any clues?

131
00:07:26,879 --> 00:07:29,620
I think Mr. Hao at the puppy beauty contest registration desk

132
00:07:29,620 --> 00:07:30,819
seems a bit suspicious.

133
00:07:30,819 --> 00:07:33,939
Oh? What's the issue?

134
00:07:33,939 --> 00:07:35,319
What's wrong?

135
00:07:35,319 --> 00:07:36,800
Hard to put into words,

136
00:07:36,800 --> 00:07:38,040
but at the contest registration,

137
00:07:38,040 --> 00:07:39,339
there's a photo

138
00:07:39,339 --> 00:07:40,560
that raised my suspicions.

139
00:07:40,560 --> 00:07:44,579
Ha! Good news—

140
00:07:44,579 --> 00:07:47,199
a boy found a lost puppy

141
00:07:47,199 --> 00:07:48,860
and brought it back.

142
00:08:02,860 --> 00:08:03,860
This isn't my dog.

143
00:08:03,860 --> 00:08:04,860
Alright, alright,

144
00:08:04,860 --> 00:08:09,900
sit down.

145
00:08:09,900 --> 00:08:14,580
Too bad the boy meant well,

146
00:08:14,580 --> 00:08:16,300
but if it's not your own dog,

147
00:08:16,300 --> 00:08:17,540
it's really hard to tell them apart.

148
00:08:17,540 --> 00:08:24,740
Why are the files all letters and numbers?

149
00:08:24,740 --> 00:08:26,780
The number of contestants is way

150
00:08:26,780 --> 00:08:28,640
beyond what we expected.

151
00:08:28,640 --> 00:08:30,680
So we have to use numbers instead.

152
00:08:30,680 --> 00:08:33,740
Now it's gotten so complicated even I can't keep track.

153
00:08:33,740 --> 00:08:35,460
Hurry up, Uncle!

154
00:08:35,460 --> 00:08:37,759
Let's go to the contest registration desk.

155
00:08:37,759 --> 00:08:39,320
I need to ask Mr. Hao a few questions.

156
00:08:48,539 --> 00:08:49,419
Huh?

157
00:08:49,539 --> 00:08:51,419
Heh heh, you're back again.

158
00:08:51,419 --> 00:08:52,980
Mr. Hao.

159
00:08:52,980 --> 00:08:54,579
I'd like to ask you a few questions.

160
00:08:54,579 --> 00:08:55,939
Sure.

161
00:08:55,939 --> 00:08:57,079
Little detective.

162
00:08:57,079 --> 00:08:59,819
How many dogs are competing in this contest?

163
00:08:59,819 --> 00:09:02,120
Uh... about...

164
00:09:02,120 --> 00:09:05,019
About three or four thousand, I'd say.

165
00:09:05,019 --> 00:09:07,500
And how many Pomeranians are participating?

166
00:09:07,500 --> 00:09:10,379
That hasn't been tallied yet.

167
00:09:10,379 --> 00:09:13,019
Probably close to a few hundred.

168
00:09:13,019 --> 00:09:15,059
With so many dogs competing,

169
00:09:15,060 --> 00:09:17,880
naturally each breed will have a lot of entries.

170
00:09:17,880 --> 00:09:21,840
So what numbering system are these dog files arranged by?

171
00:09:21,840 --> 00:09:26,780
Most of the numbers were assigned by other staff.

172
00:09:26,780 --> 00:09:28,500
I can't recall off the top of my head.

173
00:09:28,500 --> 00:09:29,560
I'd have to check.

174
00:09:29,560 --> 00:09:31,680
No need.

175
00:09:31,680 --> 00:09:34,680
Now for the last question.

176
00:09:45,060 --> 00:09:48,820
[Ending Theme Music - Full translation available in Ep. 1]

177
00:09:48,820 --> 00:09:52,300
At that time, life...

178
00:09:52,300 --> 00:09:56,760
There's bound to be some unhappiness.

179
00:09:56,760 --> 00:09:59,920
Goodbye, classic.

180
00:09:59,920 --> 00:10:04,280
It always makes you feel so down.

181
00:10:04,280 --> 00:10:07,720
Let's see what tomorrow brings.

182
00:10:07,720 --> 00:10:12,100
Waving at me from your horizon

183
00:10:12,100 --> 00:10:15,740
The sun rises and sets every day.

184
00:10:15,740 --> 00:10:19,740
Cut to a time fantasy for more.

185
00:10:19,740 --> 00:10:24,779
Looking forward to every second, every moment of life.

186
00:10:24,779 --> 00:10:31,500
Bright eyes are twinkling.

187
00:10:31,500 --> 00:10:34,879
A smile that greets the sun.

188
00:10:34,879 --> 00:10:40,100
Cross the bridge, at the silent crossroads.

189
00:10:42,100 --> 00:10:46,960
Now for the final question.

190
00:10:46,960 --> 00:10:51,080
This dog looks just like the one my wife used to have.

191
00:10:51,080 --> 00:10:54,879
Are you saying you suspect I'm the one who did the kidnapping?

192
00:10:54,879 --> 00:10:58,860
How could I ever face my late wife then?